<div class='jumbotron'>
  <h1> Evening For Us </h1>
  <% if user_signed_in?%>
    Logged in as <strong><%= current_user.email %></strong>.
    <%= link_to "Home", root_path %> |
    <%= link_to 'Edit profile', edit_user_registration_path %> |
    <%= link_to "Logout", destroy_user_session_path, method: :delete %> |
     <%= link_to 'Add Mobile Number', new_number_path %> |
     <%= link_to 'My Numbers', numbers_path %>
     <br>
     <br>

     <%= form_tag('/places/search', method:'post') do %>
     <h3> Find
       <%= text_field_tag :term, params[:term], placeholder: "Cheap food, drinks, dancing...", class: "form-control" %>
       In your city
       <%= text_field_tag :city, params[:city], placeholder: 'Boston, New York, Portland ...', class: 'form-control' %>
       By state code (two letter uppercase)
       <%= text_field_tag :state, params[:state], placeholder: "MA, NY, ME, CT, HI...", class: 'form-control' %>
       <%= submit_tag "Search", class: 'btn btn-default', name: nil %></h3>
     <% end %>
    <br>
    <br>

  <% else %>
    <%= link_to 'Login',new_user_session_path,  class:'btn btn-primary'%>
    <%= link_to 'Sign Up', new_user_registration_path, class:'btn btn-primary'%>
  <%end%>
</div>

This is my example of our first project. Evening For Us is a web app that lets the user find evening plans for themselves through yelp reviews of restaurants, bars, and night clubs. They can then send preconstructed messages to their friends with the address, time, and rating.
